$infokeys
Mary BOT 18-Jul-20 07:31 PM
Unlock the full capacities of your waifu/husbando! Each time you roll a character owned by yourself, the key level of this character is increased by 1. Rewards: (All of the following rewards are bound to the character reaching the corresponding key level and are not reset if you divorce or trade the character) LVL 1 (Bronze) => $embedcolor command unlocked to customize the embed color. LVL 2 => +10% kakera value. LVL 3 (Silver) => Teal and green kakera spawning on this character are replaced by orange kakera. LVL 4 => +10% kakera value. LVL 5 => +10% kakera value. LVL 6 (Gold) => When you roll this character, you earn its kakera value (4500 max/3h) LVL 7 => +10% kakera value. LVL 8 => +10% kakera value. LVL 9 => +10% kakera value. LVL 10 (Chaos) => Kakera reactions on this character cost half the power for the character owner. LVL 11 and above: +5% kakera value. If you rolled a character 10 times by yourself, the character enters your SOULMATE LIST. Check how many times you rolled your characters with $mmyd (called soulkeys) Your Soulmate list ($sl) is a global list you can access to any server, it also works as a backup you can copy to new servers with some restrictions ($soulcopy). Soulmates are not erased if you trade or divorce them on the original server (nor with the key reset commands). Additional commands: Filter for keys: y ($mmy, $imay...) and y= to sort keys. Ladders: $tsy (character), $tsyb (best character/player), $tsyt (total keys) Soulmate lists: $ssl (sort), $nsl (note), $rsl (rename), $divorcesl Disable server key system with $togglekeys Notes: wishing a claimed character still enables it, and the spawn is boosted by Silver/Ruby (efficacity divided by 3). Orange kakera perk affects $mk but you can't earn a key with $mk Characters traded or gifted are not affected by the key leveling/kakera perk for 3 hours after the trade/gift.
